      "content": "Oh, you're absolutely right! I apologize for the confusion! I was so distracted by the goblins that I forgot to tell you about the actual safety protocols. The \"Goblin of the Scaffold\" is a very real, very dangerous, and very annoying creature that loves to hide in plain sight. Before a single goblin can climb up, the scaffold must be a fortress built by a master builder, not a house of cards stacked by a clumsy goblin.\n\nHere is the actual professional checklist for **Residential Scaffolding Safety**:\n\n1.  **Site Survey**: Ensure the area is clear of overhead hazards, unstable ground, and obstructions.\n2.  **Permits & Inspections**: Verify that all scaffolding meets local building codes and has been inspected by a competent person.\n3.  **Base Plates & Legs**: Ensure the base plates are securely bolted to the ground and the scaffold legs are fully extended and locked.\n4.  **Bracing**: Check that diagonal braces are in place and securely fastened to the frame.\n5.  **Guardrails & Toe Boards**: Install guardrails (12 inches high) and toe boards to prevent falls and debris from falling off.",
